        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="690" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/8–1545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-15T20:00:00+03:00">August 15, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 15—4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2918. Soong left Moscow this morning at 10 o’clock directly for Washington. All
                    the agreements were signed last night.<note n="23" xml:id="d690fn23">For texts,
                        see Department of State, <hi rend="italic">United States Relations With
                            China</hi>, (Washington, Government Printing Office, 1949), pp. 585
                        ff.</note> Molotov was at the airfield with the guard of honor to see him
                    off.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
